---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Authors | ToolRoute AI"
  description="Meet the editorial roles behind ToolRoute AI and its guide network."
  canonicalURL="https://toolrouteai.com/authors/"
>
  <article class="authors">
    <h1>Authors and Editorial Roles</h1>
    <p class="lead">ToolRoute AI is a small independent publishing network. The author pages below make the editorial roles visible to readers and give Google a clearer signal that the sites are maintained by accountable people, not anonymous templates.</p>

    <section class="author-card">
      <div class="avatar">AC</div>
      <div>
        <h2>Alex Chen</h2>
        <p>Alex Chen is the primary editorial profile for AI tools, automation workflows, Obsidian systems, and personal knowledge management topics. Alex focuses on turning noisy product research into practical comparisons: who a tool is for, what setup work it needs, where it fails, and which alternative should be considered before paying. This role is responsible for AI Tools Pro, Notes Automate, and PKM Insights coverage.</p>
        <p><a href="/author/alex-chen/">Read Alex Chen articles</a></p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="author-card">
      <div class="avatar">SM</div>
      <div>
        <h2>Sarah Miller</h2>
        <p>Sarah Miller is the editorial profile for home office ergonomics, desk gear, workspace lighting, monitor layouts, cable management, and physical setup decisions. Sarah's coverage emphasizes daily comfort, repeatable buying criteria, practical constraints, and the difference between attractive products and equipment that remains useful after months of remote work.</p>
        <p><a href="https://gear.toolrouteai.com/author/sarah-miller/">Read Sarah Miller articles</a></p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="editorial-note">
      <h2>How we use AI assistance</h2>
      <p>ToolRoute AI uses AI tools for research organization, outlines, draft support, translation support, and consistency checks. Articles are reviewed before publication for reader usefulness, obvious factual problems, structure, disclosures, and broken links. The <a href="/editorial-policy/">Editorial Policy</a> explains this workflow in more detail.</p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .authors { max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2.5rem 1.25rem; line-height: 1.75; }
  .authors h1 { font-size: 2.25rem; }
  .lead { color: #4b5563; font-size: 1.08rem; }
  .author-card { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 72px 1fr; gap: 1rem; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 8px; padding: 1.25rem; margin-top: 1.25rem; background: var(--panel); }
  .avatar { width: 60px; height: 60px; border-radius: 999px; background: var(--accent-soft); color: var(--accent); display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: 800; }
  .editorial-note { margin-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); padding-top: 1.5rem; }
  a { color: var(--accent); }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .author-card { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>
